  "FootnoteData": [
    {
      "FootnoteNumber": "A1",
      "FootnoteText": "A classified attachment displaying the apportionment of specific classified programs within the amount displayed may be included.  All documents associated with this apportionment are unclassified except for the Classified Attachment.  The classified apportionment shall be allotted in full and executed without change.  Such apportionment shall remain valid during the fiscal year until such time as a reapportionment of such classified apportionment is required.  Allotments shall be made no later than 30 days after OMB signs the apportionment or the start of the subsequent calendar month, whichever is later.  [Rationale: Footnote informs that there may be a classified attachment, and provides other related requirements concerning allotments.]"
    },
    {
      "FootnoteNumber": "A2",
      "FootnoteText": "To the extent authorized by law, the amounts apportioned may be increased or decreased up to five percent of the amount on line 1000 for actual unobligated balances without further action from OMB. [Rationale: Footnote signifies that this TAFS has received or may receive an automatic apportionment.]"
    },
    {
      "FootnoteNumber": "B1",
      "FootnoteText": "(4) Funds provided by P.L. 119-21 Section 20009 paragraph 18 in the amount of $233,550,000 signed by the President July 4, 2025. (2) Funds provided by P.L. 119-21, Section 20010 paragraph 7 in the amount of $58,955,000 signed by the President July 4, 2025. (1) Funds provided by P.L. 119-21, Section 20001 paragraph 12 in the amount of $10,000,000  and paragraph 7 in the amount of $10,000,000, Section 20002 paragraph 34 in the amount of $174,000,000, Section 20005 paragraph 1 in the amount of $25,000,000 and paragraph 18 in the amount of $52,593,000, Section 20006 paragraph 1 in the amount of $75,000,000 and paragraph 2 in the amount of $100,000,000,  Section 20009 paragraph 23 in the amount of $850,000,000, Section 20010 paragraph 23 in the amount of $177,775,000 and Section 20011 paragraph 1 in the amount of $190,000,000  for a total of $1,664,368,000 signed by the President July 4, 2025."
    },
    {
      "FootnoteNumber": "B2",
      "FootnoteText": "Pursuant to section 120.21 of OMB Circular A-11, one or more lines in the Budgetary Resources section may be rounded up. As a result, those rounded lines will not match the actuals reported on the SF 133. Agency will ensure that its funds control system will only allot actuals."
    },
    {
      "FootnoteNumber": "B3",
      "FootnoteText": "Shifting the allocation of Section 20002 paragraph 34 to both FY26 and FY27."
    },
    {
      "FootnoteNumber": "B4",
      "FootnoteText": "Realigning funds from P.L. 119-21 Section 20002 paragraph 34 in the amount of $174,000,000 signed by the President July 4, 2025."
    },
    {
      "FootnoteNumber": "B5",
      "FootnoteText": "Shifting funds previoulsy apportioned into FY28 and FY29 into FY27 based on the OMB approved spend plan."
    }
